Both women are initially caught off guard and embarrassed, but quickly get over it and start making up lost time like any normal people would. The tone gets a bit more serious as the conversation shifts to the purpose of their meeting. That's when Kyouko, after years of silence, finally opens up to another person about her relationship with Wanta. The short-haired girl says she has something to show Kyouko, so they go back to her apartment. The door slowly swings open to reveal a dog waiting to greet them.
I'm not sure how I would approach the second chapter. Either short-hair girl would reveal her own story about getting into dogs and then her and Kyouko would fuck her dog together OR short-hair girl would reveal that she's never done the deed before and is looking for guidance. Considering the first half of the sequel would already have most of the sex scenes in flashback, the latter approach would probably be better. (2/2)

Theoretical Sequel: Several years after the events of the first story, Kyouko has graduated high school and her elderly pooch Wanta has passed away. Just as she vowed at the end of Mating Game, she's never told anyone about their relationship. Kyouko has since tried to move on and date men, but it's not the same, and she often finds herself reminiscing about her deceased lover. Lonely and depressed, she turns back to the internet, eventually striking up a friendship with an anonymous woman who shares her interests. After weeks of talking online, they finally agree to meet in person. In a twist of fate, it turns out to be her short-haired girlfriend from high school who seemed a little too interested in the video of the foreign girl and her dog that they stumbled across in the original story. (1/?)
